CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 29, 1966, pg. 2B, reads: "Founders Day -- Kappa Chapter of Chi Eta Phi Sorority, Inc., observed its Founders Day recently at Stouffers Restaurant in Oakland. Founded in Washington, D.C. in 1932, the sorority is an organization of professional registered nurses.  Members of Kappa Chapter are seated: Mrs. Florence Burrell and Virginia Nash.  Standing from left; Mmes. Marie Cowans, Barbara Asche, Ruth Ray, Joyce Lomax, Lillian Lesane, Dorothy Gambrell, Carrie Bullock and Wanda Johnson. -- Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of ten Chi Eta Phi members, from left, seated: Florence Burrell, Virginia Nash; standing: Marie Cowans, Barbara Asche, Ruth Ray, Joyce Lomax, Lillian Lesane, Dorothy Gambrell, Carrie Bullock, and Wanda Johnson, gathered around table in Stouffers Restaurant for Founders Day
